quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,19,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “What thing is more solemn in testimony?” Say, “Allah is Witness between you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and me. And this Recital{1}was revealed to me, that I may warn you with it, and whomever it may reach. Do you indeed testify that there are other gods with Allah?” Say, “I myself do not testify.” Say, “He is but One God, and I am indeed innocent of whatever you associate<i class=""s"">(with Him) </i>.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  6,20,"Those to whom We have brought the Scripture recognize him{1}as they recognize their own children;<i class=""s"">(those are) </i>the ones who have lost themselves, so they do not believe.",footnotes:1:The 3rd person pronoun used in Arabic can be translated to ‘him’ for the Prophet (peace be upon him) or ‘it’ for the Qur’an.
  6,21,"And who is more unjust than someone who has fabricated lies against Allah or has disbelieved in His signs? Indeed, the unjust never succeed."
  6,22,"And on the day when <span class=""h"">We herd<sup foot_note=""79974"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">them</span>all together, then say to those who associated<i class=""s"">(other gods with God) </i>, “Where are your associates whom you used to claim?”"
  6,23,"<span class=""h"">Then their only turmoil was<sup foot_note=""79975"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>when they said{2}, “<span class=""h"">By Allah, our<sup foot_note=""79977"" class=""qiraat"">3</sup> </span><span class=""h"">Lord</span>, we were not polytheists.”",footnotes:2:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  6,24,"Look how they lied to themselves, and whatever they used to fabricate strayed away from them."
  6,25,"And of them arethose who listen to you. But We have placed veils over their hearts, preventing them from comprehending it, and heaviness in their ears. Even if they see every sign, they will not believe in it. Until, when they come to you to argue with you, those who deny say, “This is nothing but legends of the ancients.”"
  6,26,"They forbid<i class=""s"">(others) </i>from it and avoid it themselves, yet they annihilate none except themselves, but they are unaware."
  6,27,"And if only you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>could see when they were<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>made to stand by the Fire and they said, “If only we could be sent back <span class=""h"">and not{1} </span>disbelieve in the signs of our Lord and be of the believers!”",footnotes:1:All except for Hafs, Hamza and Yaʻqub read it as: “If only we could be sent back—for we do not disbelieve in the signs of our Lord— and be of the believers!”
